There are 3 types of design patterns. Among those 3 types, many design patterns are included. 

    1. Behavioral - Template Method, Observer, Strategy, State, Command
    2. Creational - Singleton, Builder, Prototype, Abstract Factory, Factory Method
    3. Structural - Decorator, Flyweight, Adapter, Bridge, Facade, Proxy, Composite
    
    
Behavioral Design Patterns : This concerns with how classes and objects interact or distribute responsibility.

Creational Design Patterns : This involves object initialization and provide a way to decouple client from the objects it needs to instantiate.

Structural Design Patterns : This lets you compose classes or objects into larger structures.
